#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:17
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&FTP; is the Internet service used to transfer a data file from the disk of "
"one computer to the disk of another, regardless of the operating system type."
msgstr ""
"&FTP; je storitev Interneta, ki se uporablja za prenos podatkovnih datotek "
"iz diska enega računalnika na disk drugega, ne glede na tip operacijskega "
"sistema."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Similar to other Internet applications, &FTP; uses the client-server "
"approach &mdash; a user invokes an &FTP; program on the computer, instructs "
"it to contact a remote computer, and then requests the transfer of one or "
"more files. The local &FTP; program becomes a client that uses <acronym>TCP</"
"acronym> to contact an &FTP; server program on the remote computer. Each "
"time the user requests a file transfer, the client and the server programs "
"cooperate to send a copy of the data across the Internet."
msgstr ""
"Podobno kot druge Internetne aplikacije, &FTP; uporablja pristop strežnik-"
"odjemalec &mdash; uporabnik prikliče &FTP; program na računalniku, mu ukaže, "
"naj se poveže z oddaljenim računalnikom, in nato zahteva prenos ene ali več "
"datotek. Lokalni &FTP; program postane odjemalec, ki uporablja <acronym>TCP</"
"acronym>, da stopi v stik s &FTP; strežniškim programom na oddaljenem "
"računalniku. Vsakič, ko uporabnik zahteva prenos datoteke, strežniški in "
"odjemalski program sodelujeta, da pošljeta kopijo podatkov preko Interneta."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:31
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&FTP; servers which allow <quote>anonymous &FTP;</quote> permit any user, "
"not only users with accounts on the host, to browse the <quote>ftp</quote> "
"archives and download files. Some &FTP; servers are configured to allow "
"users to upload files."
msgstr ""
"&FTP; strežniki, ki dovoljujejo <quote>anonimen &FTP;</quote>, dovoljujejo "
"kateremu koli uporabniku, ne le tistim z računom, da brskajo po <quote>ftp</"
"quote> arhivih in prenašajo datoteke. Nekateri &FTP; strežniki so "
"skonfigurirani tako, da dovoljujejo uporabnikom tudi nalaganje datotek nanje."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:36
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&FTP; is commonly used to retrieve information and obtain software stored in "
"files at &FTP; archive sites throughout the world."
msgstr ""
"&FTP; se pogosto uporablja za pridobivanje informacij in programske opreme, "
"shranjene v datotekah na &FTP; arhivskih mestih po vsem svetu."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:41
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See the RFC: <ulink url=\"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/"
"rfc959\">https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc959</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Glejte RFC: <ulink url=\"https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/"
"rfc959\">https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc959</ulink>."

